 class MatchingStep<V,E>
extends java.lang.Object

Contains the algorithm to perform a matching step in the modified KRV procedure. Gets fractional, partion matching and exchanges fractions of flow vectors between pairs of matched vertices (the vertices are split vertices in G' and are therefore edges in the original graph G)

Author:
moritzfuchs

protected  java.lang.Double[][] performMatchingStepV2(SplitGraph<V,E> gPrime, java.util.Set<MatchedPair<SplitGraphVertex<V,E>>> matching)
          Gets a fractional, partial matching and performs an averaging step (move flow vectors depending on the weight between a pair of matched vertices) ('right' computation: for 2 Matchings (a,c,w_1) , (b,c,w_2) f_c = (1 - w_1 - w_2) * f_c + w_1 * f_a + w_2 * f_b )

Gets a fractional, partial matching and performs an averaging step (move flow vectors depending on the weight between a pair of matched vertices) ('right' computation: for 2 Matchings (a,c,w_1) , (b,c,w_2) f_c = (1 - w_1 - w_2) * f_c + w_1 * f_a + w_2 * f_b )
